# Module Purpose

Responsibilities:

- User Authentication
- User Authorization
- JWT Management
- Refresh Token Management
- Google OAuth Login
- Current User Context

The Auth module is NOT responsible for:

- User Profile Management
- Cashback Logic
- Orders
- Withdrawals
- Admin Operations

---

# Authentication Strategy

MVP Authentication Method:

Google OAuth

Flow:

User

↓

Google Login

↓

Backend Verification

↓

Create User If Needed

↓

Generate JWT

↓

Generate Refresh Token

↓

Return Tokens

---

# Supported Login Methods

Allowed:

✓ Google OAuth

Future:

- Apple Login
- Facebook Login

Not in MVP:

✗ Email Password Login

✗ Phone OTP Login

✗ Username Password Login

---

# User Entity Rules

User is the source of truth.

User must contain:

- Id
- Email
- FullName
- AvatarUrl
- Role
- Status
- LastLoginAt
- CreatedAt
- UpdatedAt

---

# User Creation Rules

On first successful Google login:

If user does not exist:

Create user.

Default values:

Role

UserRole.User

Status

UserStatus.Active

---

If user already exists:

Update:

- FullName
- AvatarUrl
- LastLoginAt

Do not create duplicate users.

Email must be unique.

---

# Roles

Use enums from:

docs/enums.md

Allowed MVP Roles:

User

Admin

Never hardcode role strings.

Bad:

```csharp
if(user.Role == "Admin")
```

Good:

```csharp
if(user.Role == UserRole.Admin)
```

---

# User Status Rules

Use enums from:

docs/enums.md

Examples:

- Active
- Suspended
- Deleted

Suspended users:

- Cannot login
- Cannot generate links
- Cannot request withdrawals

---

# JWT Rules

Authentication method:

JWT Bearer Token

---

JWT Payload Must Contain

UserId

Email

Role

IssuedAt

Expiration

---

Do not include:

- Passwords
- Secrets
- Sensitive financial data

---

# JWT Lifetime

Access Token

15 Minutes

Refresh Token

7 Days

Configurable through settings.

Never hardcode values.

---

# Refresh Token Rules

Refresh tokens must:

- Be random
- Be securely generated
- Be stored in database

---

Refresh token table:

user_refresh_tokens

Suggested fields:

- id
- user_id
- token
- expires_at
- revoked_at
- created_at

---

# Token Rotation

On refresh:

Old token

↓

Revoke

↓

Generate new token

↓

Return new pair

Reuse of revoked token should fail.

---

# Google OAuth Rules

Backend verifies Google identity.

Never trust frontend profile data.

Required:

Verify Google token server-side.

---

Required user information:

- GoogleId
- Email
- FullName
- AvatarUrl

---

Email is primary identity.

---

Auth Endpoints

Required MVP Endpoints

POST

/api/v1/auth/google-login

Purpose

Login using Google token.

---

POST

/api/v1/auth/refresh-token

Purpose

Refresh JWT.

---

POST

/api/v1/auth/logout

Purpose

Revoke refresh token.

---

GET

/api/v1/auth/me

Purpose

Current user profile.

---

