# Auth Queries

Examples

GetCurrentUserQuery

---

# Authorization Rules

Protected endpoints require:

```csharp
[Authorize]
```

Admin endpoints require:

```csharp
[Authorize(Roles = nameof(UserRole.Admin))]
```

---

Never trust:

- Request body role
- Query string role
- Frontend role

Always validate from JWT.

---

# Current User Access

Use abstraction.

Example:

ICurrentUserService

Responsibilities:

- UserId
- Email
- Role

Avoid direct HttpContext access inside handlers.

Bad:

```csharp
_httpContextAccessor.HttpContext.User
```

inside application handlers.

---

# Security Rules

Never expose:

- Refresh Tokens
- Internal Claims
- Secrets

---

Never log:

- JWT Tokens
- Refresh Tokens
- OAuth Tokens

---

All auth endpoints must support:

Rate Limiting

Examples:

Google Login

Refresh Token

---

# Frontend Rules

Frontend responsibilities:

- Google Sign-In
- Store JWT securely
- Store Refresh Token securely
- Redirect authenticated users

---

Frontend must not:

- Verify Google identity
- Make authorization decisions
- Calculate permissions

Backend remains source of truth.

---

# Protected Routes

Protected pages:

Dashboard

Orders

Withdrawals

Affiliate Links

Admin

---

Unauthenticated users:

Redirect to Login.

---

# Logout Rules

Logout must:

- Revoke refresh token
- Remove local tokens
- Clear cached user data

---

